22. Nd2 {Black played 21...Rf8 targeting [f3], after which White could have played the active 22.f4 , but they logically chose to defend with 22.Nd2 . What would you play?} Ng6 $1 {The knights are ready to occupy important squares like [f4] and [h4], strengthening the attack.} ({Editor's Note:} 22... Bd6 {(, 'refocusing the bishop toward [h2]' a tester and controlling [f4], is driven by the same idea)} 23. Rfe1 Ng6 {. ( If 23.a4 , Black can persist with 23...Ng6 . )}) 23. Rfe1 ({Not much different is} 23. Rfd1 Nef4 24. Qf1 Nxh3+ 25. Kh1 Nh4 {-+ .}) 23... Bd6 {[%csl Ye1,Ya1,Bf4][%cal Gg6f4] Now all of Black's forces have joined the attack. White's rooks are not contributing either in offence or defence; they are useless.} *

