24. f4 {A desperate 'liberation' try.} ({Also decisive is} 24. Qf1 Nef4 25. a4 Nxh3+ 26. Kh1 Nh4 27. axb5 axb5 28. Ra6 g4 {-+ .}) {Alekhine is proud and refuses to give up his arms. What do you play to counter this [f4]-push?} 24... Nexf4 25. Qf1 Nxh3+ 26. Kh1 g4 ({Editor's Note: the position is so crushing for Black that multiple continuations lead to a win, even the suboptimal} 26... Ngf4 {, leading to a simplification} 27. Bxf4 Rxf4 {.}) 27. Qe2 ({Or} 27. Qg2 Qf5 28. f3 g3 $1 29. Nf1 Nh4 30. Nxg3 Qd7 {-+ .}) 27... Qf5 {[%csl Rh5][%cal Gf5h5] White resigned as the threat of ...[Qh5] cannot be met.} 0-1

