[GameId "2130463734897805"]

23... e5 {The 'Giant-Killer' played ...[e5] in the game. How did it continue?} 24. gxf7+ Kf8 (24... Rxf7 25. Be3 a4 26. Bd5 Rcc7 27. Rg1 Kf8 28. Bxf7 {+- .}) 25. Be3 d5 26. exd5 ({White should be careful and avoid the naive} 26. Bxd5 $2 Rxc2 {∞ .}) 26... Rxf7 (26... a4 27. d6 $1 axb3 28. dxc7 {+- .}) 27. d6 $18 {Editor's Note: In an open position like this, two rooks are notoriously bad against the bishop pair – they can easily be attacked by the bishops, and the game would be over if White manages to win an exchange back. Of course, Black's king is fatally weakened too.} Rf6 {[%csl Rg5][%cal Ge3g5]} 28. Bg5 Qb7 29. Bxf6 Bxf6 30. d7 Rd8 31. Qd6+ (31. Qd6+ {Black resigned due to} Kg7 32. Rg1+ Kh7 33. Qxf6 {+- .}) ({There was a quicker win by} 31. Qh6+ Ke7 {(31...Bg7 32.Qd6)} 32. Qh7+ Bg7 33. Qxg7# {.}) 1-0

