1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. e3 Be7 5. b3 O-O 6. Bb2 c5 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8. Nxd5 Qxd5 9. Bc4 Qd8 10. Ne5 Nd7 11. O-O Nxe5 12. Bxe5 Bf6 13. d4 cxd4 14. exd4 Bd7 15. Qh5 Bc6 16. Rad1 Be4 17. Rfe1 Bc2 18. Rd2 Bg6 19. Qe2 Be7 20. Rdd1 Qb6 21. d5 exd5 22. Rxd5 Bf6 23. Rd6 Qc5 {White is active but a solution must be found, as sooner or later his initiative will evaporate.} 24. Rxf6 $1 {An excellent exchange sacrifice, aiming for the attack.} ({Note from a tester:} 24. Rd5 {is objectively better. After} Qe7 25. Qd2 Bxe5 26. Rdxe5 {.}) 24... gxf6 25. Bxf6 {Now the black king is rather weak on the dark squares and the continuous threat of the white queen on [h6] is annoying...} *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
