[GameId "2130463734951058"]

{This move found by Trifunović was not the best. Black should try to defend with Qc6 Qb2! Rfe8 Rd1 (27.Rc1 Qd6 (27...b5? 28.Bh8 Kf8 29.Bg7+ Kg8 30.Bh6 +-) 28.Qa1 Rac8 29.Rd1= ∞) Be4 f3 b5 Bh8 Qc5+ Kh1 Qg5 Bf6 Qh5 Be2 ⩲ .} 25... Qh5 $2 {What would you play in response to this suboptimal move?} 26. g4 $1 ({This is even better than the game's} 26. Qe3 {.}) 26... Qh3 27. f3 {The black rooks cannot really move... White should try to capitalize on Black’s weak pawns and more exposed king.} (27. f3 {Black's best answers include ...b5 and ...h5, for instance} b5 28. Bxb5 h5 29. Bd7 hxg4 30. fxg4 {, and White's bishops are dominating.}) (27. f3 {The suboptimal} Rac8 {can be met by} 28. Qe3 {, thinking of an eventual Bf1, chasing the queen,} Rc6 29. Bd4 {.}) *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
