[White "2) The Attack on the King Concept"]
[Black "Smyslov vs. Trifunović #3"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "r4rk1/pp3p1p/5Bb1/7q/2B5/1P6/P3QPPP/4R1K1 w - - 0 26"]
[PlyCount "9"]
[GameId "2130463734959251"]

26. Qe3 (26. g4 $1 Qh3 27. f3 {(looks even better! As we saw in the previous variation. The black rooks cannot really move...)}) 26... h6 $2 {This nearly loses.} ({Black had to opt for} 26... b5 27. Bxb5 {(( 27.Bd5 is better 27...Qf5 28.Bxa8 Qxf6 29.Bf3 ± . ))} Qf5 28. Qe5 Qxe5 29. Rxe5 {± and hope...}) {How could have played the seventh World Chess Champion in this position?} 27. Bb2 $1 ({The text move} 27. h3 $6 {preserved the advantage, but this is killing.}) 27... Kh7 28. Qd4 Rg8 29. Re5 Rad8 30. Bd5 $18 {[%cal Rd8d5,Gd4d5,Yh5h4] The best way for Black to save their queen is by sacrificing the exchange.} *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
