1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 4. O-O Be7 5. c4 O-O 6. d4 dxc4 7. Qc2 a6 8. a4 Bd7 9. Qxc4 Bc6 10. Bg5 a5 11. Nc3 Na6 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. e4 Nb4 14. Rfd1 Ra6 15. Rac1 Rb6 16. h4 h6 17. Qe2 Re8 18. Rd2 Qd7 19. Qd1 Qd8 20. Nh2 Be7 21. Ng4 Rf8 22. Ne5 Be8 23. Bf1 Rd6 24. Nc4 Ra6 25. Ne3 Ra8 26. d5 e5 27. Nf5 Bc5 28. Bb5 Kh7 29. Bxe8 Rxe8 30. Nb5 b6 {With all of White's pieces well-placed, Smbat Lputian initiates combinative play.} 31. d6 $1 ({Note from Chessable:} 31. Rxc5 {is an excellent move as well,} bxc5 32. d6 {.}) 31... Bxd6 $2 {This isn't advisable.} (31... c6 32. Nc7 {+-}) 32. Nbxd6 cxd6 33. Rxd6 Qb8 34. Rxh6+ $1 gxh6 35. Qh5 $18 {Mate in two.} *

