31... cxd6 (31... c6 32. Nc7 {+- and 31...Bxd6? 32.Nbxd6 cxd6 33.Rxd6 Qb8 34.Rxh6+! gxh6 35.Qh5 +- are not advisable.}) {In the game, the future co-author of Game Changer played 31...Bxd6? . What should White have played in response to 31...cxd6 ?} 32. Rxc5 $1 (32. Nbxd6 Re6 33. Nxf7 Qf6 34. Rd7 {is good enough for White, but the exchange sacrifice destroys Black's position for good. And this is quite natural, as the black [c5]-bishop is the most important defensive black piece, guarding a lot of important squares in Black's camp.}) 32... bxc5 33. Rxd6 Qb8 34. Rxh6+ $1 gxh6 35. Qh5 {A common method to mate in this game!} *

