33... Qc8 {We are now in a subvariation of the previous line. What should play White in this position?} 34. Qh5 {[%csl Rh6,Rf7][%cal Gh5f7,Gd6h6] Now White is attacking with three pieces Qh5, Rd6, Nf5 while Black cannot really defend properly, as his rooks as well as the distant [b4]-knight are only physically present at the board, hardly participating in the battle!} ({Of course, not} 34. Rxh6+ $2 gxh6 35. Qh5 Qe6 {-+ .}) 34... Ra6 ({Alternatives like} 34... Re6 35. Qxf7 {+- ,}) ({or} 34... f6 35. Rxf6 gxf6 36. Qf7+ Kh8 37. Qg7# {,}) ({or, finally,} 34... Kg8 35. Rxh6 $1 gxh6 36. Qg4+ Kh8 37. Qg7# {, also fail to defend.}) 35. Qxf7 Rg8 36. Qg6+ Kh8 37. Rxa6 (37. Rxa6 {Black resigned due to} Qxa6 {(( 37...Nxa6 38.Nbd6 +- ))} 38. Nbd6 Qa7 39. Nf7+ {+- . A nice attacking game in which, once again, quality outplayed quantity.}) 1-0

