[PlyCount "14"]
[GameId "2130463735164066"]

28. Red1 {" Always put the rook behind the pawn... " In the game, Nikolić correctly followed Tarrasch's rule. What is the only winning move? Try calculating a few moves ahead.} Nh6 $1 {Good play by Black.} ({The naive} 28... Ngxh4 $2 29. Be4 $1 {would allow White to form a kind of defence.}) 29. Qe2 Nf4 30. Qc4 {Although his position is lost, White should have tried to exchange queens. That's what we will see in this variation.} ({In the game Predrag Nikolić played} 30. Qd2 $6 {. See the following variation.}) 30... e5 (30... Bf3 31. Rd3 Nxd3 32. Qxd3 Bb7 {-+}) 31. Qc7 Ne2+ $1 {Black would have to find this killing blow.} 32. Nxe2 (32. Kh2 Ng4+ 33. Kh3 Nf4#) 32... Qd5 33. Kf1 Qh1+ 34. Ng1 Bf3 $19 *

