15. Ne5 $2 {A rather optimistic idea.} ({White had to concentrate on his defence by} 15. Rg1 f4 16. b3 Bd5 {∞ .}) 15... Rg8 $2 {Black failed to make use of White's bad move.} (15... Nc6 $1 16. Nxc6 Bxc6 17. Rg1 f4 {∓ looks strong.}) 16. f4 Nc6 17. Nf3 Na5 $1 {[%cal Ga5b3] Not only blocks the a-file, but it is getting ready to land on [b3] when in need.} 18. Kf2 Nb3 19. Ra7 $1 Qb6 {This is objectively the best move, but Black didn't like the following continuation:} (19... Be4 $6 {was played in the game.}) 20. Rxb7 Qxb7 21. g3 Nd2 {[%csl Rh1]} (21... Bd6 $5 22. Bg2 Qa7 23. Qe2 Ke7 {∞}) 22. Nxd2 $1 Qxh1 23. Nf3 Ke7 24. Qa1 $1 {[%csl Ra7,Yh1] White should have sufficient compensation due to 'badly' placed black queen.} *

