[PlyCount "41"]
[GameId "2130463735250088"]

23... Qd5 $6 (23... Bd5 {was simple and effective:} 24. Kf2 Qb6 25. Rf1 Nxd4 {-+ .}) 24. g3 $6 (24. Rg1 {looks like a good defending move, but still Black gets to the top after} Rg4 {-+ .}) 24... Nxd4 $2 ({Black failed to find the killing continuation} 24... Rg4 $1 25. Kf2 Bf5 26. Rf1 Nxd4 {-+ .}) 25. Nxd4 $2 {And White returned the favour in no time!} (25. Ra8+ $1 Qxa8 26. Qxd4 Bf5 27. Rd1 {would be unclear and just a mess; a good sign for White by the way!}) 25... Bxh1 26. Bf3 Qxe5+ 27. Kf2 Bc5 $1 28. Bxh1 (28. Ra8+ {loses to} Ke7 29. Rxg8 Bxd4+ 30. Kf1 Qe3 $1 31. Qxd4 Qxd4 32. Bxh1 Qxb2 {-+ .}) 28... Bxd4+ 29. Kf1 Rg5 $6 ({Black wants to continue the attack, but} 29... Qe3 $1 30. Qe2 Qxe2+ 31. Kxe2 Ke7 {-+ leads to a winning endgame for Black.}) 30. Bf3 $6 (30. b4 $1 {to allow the [a2]-rook to join the defence, was a must. After} Rf5+ 31. Bf3 Kf8 32. Kg2 Rf6 33. Rd2 Bb6 {, Black will prevail, but a lot of work will be needed.}) 30... Kf8 31. Kg2 Qe3 32. Kh3 Kg7 $6 ({Again,} 32... Qf2 $1 33. Qe2 Qxe2 34. Bxe2 Rf5 {-+ was curtains.}) 33. b3 $1 cxb3 $2 {Another dubious move.} ({Good was} 33... c3 $1 34. Qe2 b4 {, when Black would be on the right track.}) 34. Ra3 $1 b4 $1 35. Rxb3 Bc3 36. Qe2 Qc5 37. Qd3 $6 ({Time-trouble didn't help White to find the stubborn defence by} 37. Qe4 $1 Re5 38. Qg4+ Rg5 39. Qe4 Qb5 40. Kg2 {∓ .}) 37... Qc8+ 38. Kg2 Ra5 39. Qc2 $2 {But the text is decisive.} ({The only way for White was by} 39. Rb1 Ra2+ 40. Kh1 Qh3 41. Be2 Qe6 {∓ .}) 39... Qe6 40. Qb1 Ra1 41. Qc2 Bd4 $1 {The mating attack cannot be avoided.} 42. Bd1 Qe1 43. Bf3 Qf1# 0-1

