1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 dxe4 5. Nxe4 Nbd7 6. Nf3 h6 7. Nxf6+ Nxf6 8. Be3 Bd6 9. Bd3 b6 10. Qe2 Bb7 11. O-O-O Nd5 12. Ne5 Qf6 13. Bb5+ c6 14. Bxc6+ Bxc6 15. Nxc6 O-O 16. Ne5 Rfc8 17. Nd3 a5 18. Qf3 Qg6 19. a3 Ra7 20. Kd2 Rac7 21. Rc1 b5 22. g3 {Black sacrificed a pawn in order to grab the initiative. All his pieces are well-placed and are pressurising White's queenside, so his compensation must be satisfactory.} b4 $1 23. axb4 (23. a4 Nb6 24. b3 Nd5 {∓ .}) 23... Rxc2+ $1 ({Although Black retains the advantage after both} 23... axb4 24. Rhd1 Rc4 {⩱ and 23...Nxb4 24.Nxb4 axb4 25.c3 e5 ∓ ( 25.Qd1 e5 ∓ ) , his exchange sacrifice is to the point and meets the needs of the position. And of course, it is principally aimed against the white king.}) 24. Rxc2 Rxc2+ 25. Kxc2 Nxb4+ {Editor's Note: To be continued in the next exercises.} *

