1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 a6 6. b3 Bb4 7. Bd2 Nbd7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O Bd6 10. e4 dxc4 11. bxc4 e5 12. c5 Bc7 13. Na4 exd4 14. h3 Re8 15. Re1 h6 16. Rb1 Nf8 17. Qc1 Rb8 18. Rb4 Ne6 19. Rc4 Ba5 20. Bxa5 Qxa5 21. Nxd4 Nxd4 22. Rxd4 Qc7 23. Rd6 Be6 24. Nb6 Red8 25. e5 Ne8 {When White decided on his 23rd move, he made a 'commitment' for the exchange sacrifice.} 26. Qf4 $1 Qe7 27. Re3 Nxd6 28. cxd6 {There is tremendous positional compensation for White's sacrifice - great minor pieces, lack of scope for the rooks, a powerful passed pawn and so on. However, even more important is that now that the knight has left [f6] a very strong attack will virtually play itself.} *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
