[PlyCount "25"]
[GameId "2130463735336110"]

28... Qg5 {It is time to show the tremendous positional compensation for White's sacrifice. What would you play? Can you foresee what the next sequence will be?} 29. Qe4 {Keeping the queens on is essential in the attack.} g6 30. Rg3 {Lining up the rook against the heavy black pieces.} Bf5 31. Qf3 Qc1+ 32. Kh2 Bxd3 33. e6 $18 {No need to lose time!} Qc5 (33... fxe6 {would lose to} 34. Qxd3 Kh8 35. Qxg6 Rg8 36. Qf6+ Kh7 37. Qf7+ Kh8 38. Nd7 {+- .}) 34. Qxf7+ Kh8 35. Qf6+ Kh7 36. Rxd3 Qxb6 {Black is now even a rook up, but the white pawn duo on the 6th rank decides the game.} 37. Qf7+ Kh8 38. Qxg6 Qxf2 39. Qxh6+ Kg8 40. e7 Rd7 (40... Rd7 {Black resigned due to} 41. Qg6+ Kh8 42. e8=Q+ Rxe8 43. Qxe8+ Kg7 44. Qxd7+ {+- .}) 1-0

