23. h3 Kd7 ({Black will need the assistance of his king, but possible is the immediate} 23... Qh4 24. Qe5 Qf6 25. Qe3 {(25.Qxf6 gxf6 26.Rxa4? bxa4 27.Rb8+ Kd7 28.Rxh8 a3 -+)} Kd7 {∓ .}) 24. Re1 Qh4 $1 {Black must win the [d6]-pawn, but must also eliminate any dangerous counterplay his opponent might drum up. That's the reason why he should try to exchange the queens.} *

