1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. f3 O-O 6. Be3 Nc6 7. Qd2 a6 8. Nge2 Re8 9. Nc1 e5 10. d5 Nd4 11. N1e2 c5 12. dxc6 Nxc6 13. Nd5 {White seems to be doing great by now...} b5 $1 ({An almost forced exchange sacrifice, as after} 13... Nxd5 $6 14. cxd5 Ne7 15. Nc3 {± (, White enjoys a pleasant advantage. Black is obliged to take such decisions from time to time at least! in order not to fall into passivity, even if the engine disagrees.)}) 14. Bb6 ({White is in no position to choose:} 14. Nec3 Nd4 15. Bd3 {(15.Nxf6+? Bxf6 16.cxb5 axb5 17.Bxb5 Bh4+ ∓)} Be6 {∞ .}) 14... Qd7 15. Nc7 Rb8 16. Nxe8 Qxe8 {So, what has Black achieved with his decision? 1. Better development.2. Active play for his pieces. These two facts do not seem worth much, but White is facing some other problems: 3. He will need time to complete his development. 4. He will lose some tempi to protect his pieces in the meantime. Actually, what Black 'bought' is time and initiative.} *

