26... Rf5 27. Bc4+ (27. Nxe4 {looks good as well, threatening [Nd6].}) 27... Kf8 28. Rc7 Rxg5 29. Nxc8 Rf5 30. Nd6 Rf4 ({The alternative was} 30... Rf6 {and after} 31. Nxe4 Rf4 32. Nd6 {, to return the exchange with} Rd8 33. g3 Rxd6 34. gxf4 Rd1+ 35. Kg2 Rd4 {, but White should win either with} 36. Rf7+ {( or simply with 36.Bb3 +-)} Ke8 37. Rxg7 Rxc4 38. Rxb7 {+- .}) 31. g3 Rf3 32. Nxe4 $18 {White has got a pawn as well, and his initiative remains strong.} h6 33. Kg2 Rf5 34. h4 Rd8 (34... Ne8 {was perhaps better, but in the long run Black is doomed:} 35. Rd7 b6 36. cxb6 Rxb6 37. a3 {± .}) 35. Rxb7 Rd4 36. Nd6 Rf6 37. Rb8+ Ke7 38. Nc8+ (38. Bxa6 Nf5 39. Re8+ Kd7 40. Bc8+ Kc7 41. Bxf5 gxf5 42. a3 {was a lost case for Black.}) 38... Kd7 39. Nb6+ Kc7 (39... Ke7 40. Rb7+ Kf8 41. Nd7+ {+- wins the exchange back, so White will remain with two extra pawns.}) 40. Ra8 Ne6 41. Bxa6 $6 ({The more accurate} 41. Re8 Rd2 42. Re7+ Kd8 43. Rxe6 Rfxf2+ 44. Kh3 {was curtains.}) 41... Rf8 42. Bc8 Nd8 $6 ({Black should try his last chance:} 42... Rf6 43. a3 Rd2 44. Kh3 {± and hope. And he surely should avoid now} Rfxf2 $2 45. Ra7+ $1 {(45.Bxe6? h5 46.Ra7+ Kb8 47.Ra8+ Kc7=)} Kd8 46. Bxe6 h5 47. Rd7+ {+- .}) 43. Bd7 Kb7 (43... Rxb4 {was losing to} 44. Rc8+ Kb7 45. Bxc6+ Nxc6 46. Rxf8 {+- .}) 44. Rc8 Rxd7 45. Nxd7 Re8 46. Nb6 g5 47. hxg5 hxg5 48. a4 g4 49. Ra8 {Black resigned, as [a5]-[a6]+ and [Rc8] mate will follow.} 1-0

