23. Kf2 $2 (23. Bc4 {was the last practical chance, but Black must be winning in the long run after} Bxe3+ 24. Kh1 Nb4 25. Ra1 Bc5 26. Rxa3 Nxd5 27. Rb3 {( After 27.Rd3 Ne7 , Black should have enough material plus to win. )} Ne7 {, due to his powerful bishops.}) 23... Nb4 24. Rc1 (24. Rd1 {doesn't help due to} Nc2 {(24...Ba7 25.Bc4 Nc2 26.Rd3 Bf5 27.Rc3 Nxe3 28.Rxe3 Bb1 29.d6 Kf8 30.d7 Bxe3+ 31.Kxe3 Ke7 -+)} 25. Rxd4 Nxd4 26. Bc4 Bd7 {-+ .}) 24... a2 $1 25. Rxc8+ Kg7 26. Rc1 Nxd5 27. Rd1 Nxe3 {[%csl Rd1,Rf2][%cal Yd1d4,Ga2a1]} (27... Nxe3 {Black resigned due to} 28. Rxd4 a1=Q 29. Kxe3 Qg1+ {+ -+ . Good 'preparation' by Vladimir Kramnik.}) 0-1

