1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. g3 dxc4 6. a4 e6 7. Bg2 c5 8. O-O cxd4 9. Nxd4 Nbd7 10. Nc2 Qc7 11. Bf4 e5 12. Bd2 Nc5 13. Bg5 Be6 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Nd5 Qd8 16. Nce3 Nb3 17. a5 Rc8 18. Ra4 Nd4 19. Nb6 Rc7 {What did Kramnik play?} 20. Rxc4 $1 ({This strong move was admittedly underestimated by Black, who was only expecting} 20. Nexc4 $2 Bg4 {∞ (. The idea is to dominate on the light squares and also benefit from the bad position of the black king and what about the doubled f-pawns and the weak black kingside?.)}) 20... Bxc4 ({Black is obliged to accept the sac, as after} 20... Bc5 21. Nbd5 Rc8 22. Qd3 {, he would be just plain worse.}) 21. Nexc4 {Probably not the best, although there is no good advice one can give:} Bc5 ({Or} 21... Be7 22. e3 Ne6 23. Qa4+ Kf8 24. Nd5 {± .}) 22. e3 Bxb6 23. Nxb6 $16 *

