24. e3 {The text move looks very human, just stopping Black's only active idea ...[Nd4] and White slowly starts to improve his position.} ({But the direct} 24. Ne3 Nd4 25. Ned5 Nxe2+ 26. Kf1 {+- was just killing!}) 24... Be7 {" Black has no moves practically, so from now on, White just has to choose which of many attractive possibilities to play. – Vladimir Kramnik "} 25. Qf5 Kf8 26. Bd5 Kg7 27. Qg4+ Kh6 28. e4 ({Playing for direct mate, although} 28. Bxf7 {+- was good as well.}) 28... Nd4 29. Ne3 ({(The 14th World Chess Champion noted : 'I was already looking for mate, not paying too much attention to the other side of the board, but in fact, our silicon friend enemy? discovers a very nice geometrical motif instead:)} 29. b4 $1 Qxb4 30. Rxd4 exd4 31. Qf4+ Kg7 32. Qxc7 {, winning. '}) 29... f5 30. Qh3+ Kg7 31. Rxd4 $1 exd4 32. Nxf5+ Kf8 33. Qh6+ Ke8 {Black is under heavy attack, and White has an easy task to finish off his opponent...} 34. Bxf7+ $1 Kd8 (34... Kxf7 35. Qg7+ {+-}) 35. Qg7 Rf8 36. Nxd4 (36. Nd5 {is good enough as well.}) 36... Rc6 (36... Rxf7 37. Qxf7 Qxd4 38. Qg8+ Bf8 39. Qxf8# {.}) 37. Nxc6+ bxc6 (37... Qxc6 38. Qxh7 Bf6 39. Nd5 {+- .}) 38. Qg4 $1 Kc7 {Otherwise, White mates on [d7] or [c8].} 39. Qd7+ Kb8 40. Qd2 $2 {A wrong attitude, based on Black's time-trouble.} ({Correct was} 40. Qe6 Rd8 41. Nd7+ Rxd7 42. Qxd7 {+- ,}) ({or simply} 40. Kg2 {+- .}) 40... Kc7 (40... Bg5 $5 {was an incredibly tricky move, which wouldn't save the game, but at least prolong it. White wins with} 41. Nd7+ Kc8 $1 42. Qd1 $1 Rd8 43. Qg4 $1 Qe7 {(43...Rxd7 44.Be6 +-)} 44. Nf6+ Kb7 45. Qxg5 Qxf7 46. e5 {+- .}) 41. Qd7+ Kb8 42. Kg2 $1 Bd6 {There was no defence any more for Black.} ({Alternatives like} 42... Rd8 43. Qxd8+ Bxd8 44. Nd7+ Ka7 45. Nxc5 {+- ,}) ({or} 42... Rxf7 43. Qc8+ Ka7 44. Qc7# {, were just plain losing as well.}) 43. b4 $1 Qd4 44. Qxc6 {" White has a number of wins on every next move. Usually, I am quite strong when I am five pawns up. – Vladimir Kramnik "} Ka7 45. Kh3 Qd1 46. Nc8+ Rxc8 47. Qxc8 Qf1+ 48. Kg4 h5+ 49. Kxh5 1-0

