1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. f3 O-O 6. Bg5 c5 7. d5 e6 8. Qd2 exd5 9. cxd5 a6 10. a4 Nbd7 11. Nh3 Re8 12. Be2 Ne5 13. Nf2 Qc7 14. O-O Rb8 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 {Editor's Note: Although the following motif is off-topic, it's a great positional weapon for White in King's Indian/Benoni structures.} 16. f4 Nd7 {[%csl Rb8,Rc8]} 17. e5 dxe5 18. d6 Qd8 19. Nfe4 Bg7 $2 20. f5 $18 {[%csl Ge4,Re5][%cal Gc3d5,Ge2c4] Editor's Note: Three of Black's pieces are obstructed by his [e5]-pawn: the [g7]-bishop, [d7]-knight and [e8]-rook. Meanwhile, White has great potential activity on the light squares: the [e4]-knight is well placed, the bishop can come to [c4] and the [c3]-knight can come to [d5]. On top of that, the f-file will be opened too.} *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4) The Open File Concept"]
[Black "Adianto vs. Gunawan #2"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "1rbqr1k1/1p1n1pbp/p2P2p1/2p1pP2/P3N3/2N5/1P1QB1PP/R4RK1 b - - 0 20"]
[PlyCount "6"]
[GameId "2130463735971037"]

20... gxf5 21. Rxf5 Nf8 22. Raf1 $1 {A nice positional exchange sacrifice, aiming mostly to stop an eventual ...[f5]. Also, without the light-squared bishop, it would be very difficult for Black to defend his king. Keep in mind that a passed d-pawn exists, which is ready to advance. All these advantages are surely more than adequate compensation for the small deficit of an exchange.} ({Editor's Note: The engine sees no reason to give the exchange and much prefers} 22. Rh5 {or 22.Rf2 . However, we must always strive to play principled chess, and White still has a good advantage. Black has 1 defender less now, whereas White only 'replaced' the attacker – the [a1]-rook was not participating in the attack anyway.}) 22... Bxf5 23. Rxf5 $16 {White dominates the light square complexes in the centre and on the kingside, and his pieces generally control important squares. Take a look at the black rooks; don't they look miserable?} *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4) The Open File Concept"]
[Black "Adianto vs. Gunawan #3"]
[Result "1-0"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "1r1qrnk1/1p3pbp/p2P4/2p1pR2/P3N3/2N5/1P1QB1PP/6K1 b - - 0 23"]
[PlyCount "10"]
[GameId "2130463735979230"]

23... Ne6 $6 (23... f6 24. Nd5 Nd7 25. Rh5 {with the idea [Bg4]-[f5], is not ideal,}) ({but} 23... Qd7 24. Rg5 Kh8 25. Bg4 Ne6 26. Rh5 {is an unpleasant, but probably compulsory option for Black.}) 24. Nd5 $1 {The white pieces are dancing on the light squares!} Nd4 {The text move doesn't help.} ({Neither do the other options:} 24... Rf8 25. Ndf6+ Bxf6 26. Nxf6+ Kg7 27. Qe3 $1 Qxf6 28. Rxf6 Kxf6 29. Qh6+ Kf5 30. Qxh7+ Kf6 31. Bg4 {+- ,}) ({or} 24... Nf4 25. Bc4 Rf8 {(25...Nxd5 26.Qxd5 Qh4 27.g3 Qg4 28.Rxf7 Kh8 29.d7 +-)} 26. Ndf6+ Kh8 27. g3 b5 28. gxf4 bxc4 29. fxe5 {+- .}) 25. Ndf6+ Kh8 (25... Bxf6 26. Nxf6+ Kg7 27. Qg5+ Kh8 28. Qh6 {+- ,}) ({or} 25... Kf8 26. Nxh7+ Kg8 27. Nef6+ Kh8 28. Rh5 Nxe2+ 29. Qxe2 {+- .}) 26. Rh5 Nxe2+ 27. Kf1 $1 Bxf6 ({Black is mated after} 27... Qxf6+ 28. Nxf6 Bxf6 29. Qh6 Kg8 30. Qxh7+ Kf8 31. Rg5 {+- ,}) ({or} 27... h6 28. Rxh6+ {+- .}) 28. Qh6 (28. Qh6 {Black resigned due to} Kg8 29. Qxh7+ {(29.Nxf6+ Qxf6+ 30.Qxf6 Nf4 31.Rf5 +-)} Kf8 30. Rg5 $1 Qxd6 31. Nxd6 {+- .}) 1-0

