[PlyCount "6"]
[GameId "2130463736016099"]

23... Rc8 ({Maybe the lesser evil was} 23... Qxc5 $5 24. Bxc5 Rd7 25. Bxa7 {(25.dxe6 fxe6 26.Nxe6 b6 ⩲)} Ra8 26. b6 {±}) ({A spectacular queen sacrifice occurs after} 23... Qd8 24. dxe6 fxe6 25. Qxa7 b6 26. a5 $1 {(26.Rc1? Ra8 27.Qb7 Rb8=)} Ra8 {(26...bxa5 27.Rc1 Ra8 28.Qc5 ±)} 27. axb6 $1 Rxa7 28. bxa7 {± , putting Black in deep trouble, as analysis shows:} Qa8 29. Rb1 {± .}) 24. Qxa7 b6 25. Qxc7 Rxc7 26. Rd1 $1 {White's two central pawns and the activity of his pieces give him more than enough compensation for the sacrificed exchange; they give him a clear advantage!} *

