26... Bf6 $2 {An error in an already difficult position.} ({Even worse was} 26... Nc4 $2 27. Rc1 {+- ,}) ({but Black could have tried} 26... g5 $5 27. Nh5 h6 28. g3 {± .}) {How do you punish that move?} 27. dxe6 Rxd1+ {The best course of action.} 28. Bxd1 fxe6 29. Bb3 $1 {[%csl Re6] White's advantage is obviously decisive as he wins a third pawn, so Black resigns. An impressive performance!} 1-0

