1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 c6 4. Nf3 d5 5. h3 Nf6 6. Bd3 dxe4 7. Nxe4 Nxe4 8. Bxe4 Nd7 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1 c5 11. c3 cxd4 12. cxd4 Nf6 13. Bc2 Be6 {How a player reacts to temptation is a strong indicator of their strength. Knowing the subject of this chapter, should you give in to temptation?} 14. Rxe6 $1 {An interesting exchange sacrifice with multiple aims: 1. To destroy Black's pawn structure. 2. To create a strong outpost on [e5]. 3. To obtain the bishop pair. 4. To take over the initiative.} fxe6 15. Ng5 $1 ({After} 15. Qe2 $6 Qd5 16. Bb3 Qe4 17. Bxe6+ Kh8 {, Black succeeds at least in exchanging queens.}) 15... Qd5 $2 (15... Qb6 16. Qe2 Nh5 $1 {(16...Bh6?! 17.Nxe6 Bxc1 18.Nxf8 Bxb2 19.Nd7! Nxd7 20.Bb3+ Kf8 21.Qxb2 ±)} 17. Nxe6 Bxd4 18. Nxf8 {(18.Nxd4!? Qxd4 19.Bb3+ Kh8 20.Be3 ⩲)} Rxf8 19. Bb3+ Kh8 20. Be3 Bxe3 21. Qxe3 Qxe3 22. fxe3 {⩲ .}) 16. Bb3 $18 *

