16... Qd7 (16... Rf6 17. Qe2 Qd7 18. Re1 {± .}) 17. Qg4 $1 (17. Qe2 e5 $1 18. dxe5 Qc8 {is helping Black.}) 17... Rf5 $5 ({Black already faces too many problems as alternatives prove:} 17... Rf6 18. Re1 Bh6 19. Ne4 Rf7 20. Nc5 {± ,}) ({or} 17... Nf6 18. Qe2 Rfe8 19. Nxe6 Bh8 20. Bb3 Nd5 21. c4 {+- . His decision to return the exchange is probably best.}) 18. Re1 Nf6 19. Bxf5 $1 exf5 (19... Nxg4 $2 20. Bxe6+ Qxe6 21. Nxe6 Nf6 {(21...Nh6 22.Nxg7 Kxg7 23.Rxe7+ +-)} 22. Nxg7 {+-} Kxg7 23. Rxe7+ {+- .}) 20. Qd1 $18 {Material has been restored but Black's weaknesses along the e-file are serious.} *

