1. e4 c6 2. c4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. cxd5 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nxc3 7. bxc3 g6 8. d4 Bg7 9. Bd3 O-O 10. O-O Nc6 11. Re1 Re8 12. Bg5 Be6 {Be6 is natural move. Black intends to play ...[Rc8], ...[Na5] and hit the [c3]-pawn as well as gain an outpost on [c4]...} 13. Rxe6 $1 {So, here it comes again! What does White gain out of this exchange sacrifice? Black has a weakened king position and some bad pawns, and he will be put on the defensive.} fxe6 14. Bc4 Qd6 15. Qe2 Nd8 16. Re1 $16 {Natural attacking moves give White the initiative.} Rc8 17. Nd2 {A good way to continue the attack.} ({Getting greedy with the naive} 17. Bxe6+ $2 Nxe6 18. Qxe6+ Qxe6 19. Rxe6 Rxc3 {, is just plain bad for White - he didn't even win a pawn...}) 17... Kh8 18. Ne4 Qc7 19. Bb3 *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
