1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6 7. f3 b5 8. Qd2 Nbd7 9. O-O-O Bb7 10. g4 Nb6 11. Qf2 Nfd7 12. Kb1 Rc8 13. Bd3 {Only one move gives Black a slight advantage.} Rxc3 $1 {The idea is simple: destroy the opponent's pawn structure and prepare for a complicated middlegame. White's compromised queenside pawn structure offers great attacking chances to Black.} *

