21. b4 {White is desperate to find a plan, so he tries to open the b-file for his rooks. But on the other hand, he will have to give Black a passed and protected pawn on [c5].} Nxf3+ 22. Bxf3 h5 $1 {With the idea ...[h4], weakening the white king's defence.} 23. bxc5 bxc5 24. Qd2 Ne5 25. Be2 Bc8 $17 {The [b7]-bishop was doing nothing on [b7], so it is transferred to the kingside, assisting a potential attack.} 26. Rb1 Bh3 27. Nd1 Re8 28. Nf2 Bc8 29. Kg2 Bh6 (29... h4 30. g4 c4 31. Rec1 Bh6 {∓ was another way to proceed.}) 30. Rb3 f5 $2 ({There was no need to un-double the white e-pawns, so} 30... h4 {(was as mentioned beforehand the right continuation.)}) 31. exf5 Bxf5 32. Qb2 $1 Bc8 33. e4 Bg7 34. Qc2 Rf8 35. Rf1 h4 $1 {Finally!} 36. Nh3 hxg3 $2 ({It was time to accept that Black has lost his advantage and make a draw by means of} 36... c4 $1 37. Bxc4 Bxh3+ 38. Kxh3 Qd7+ 39. Kg2 Rc8 40. Rc3 Ng4 41. Rcf3 $1 Ne5 42. Rc3 {.}) 37. Rxf8+ $2 ({Good was} 37. hxg3 Bxh3+ 38. Kxh3 Rxf1 39. Bxf1 Qg5 40. Be2 {± . Still, it is not easy for White to prove his advantage, but he would be on the right track.}) 37... Qxf8 38. Rxg3 Bh6 $6 (38... Bxh3+ $1 {was the right way to go for. After} 39. Rxh3 Qf4 40. Rg3 Bh6 {∞ , Black should have enough compensation for his investment to preserve the balance, but not really for more.}) 39. Ng5 $1 Bxg5 40. Rxg5 Qf4 41. Rg3 Kg7 42. Kg1 Bd7 43. Kg2 ({White could have opted for} 43. Bf1 Bg4 44. Bg2 Bf3 45. Bxf3 Nxf3+ 46. Kh1 Ne5 47. Qb1 {⩲ .}) 43... Be8 44. Bd3 g5 $1 {A good idea, turning [e4]-pawn into a target.} 45. Qf2 Bg6 46. Bc2 (46. Qxf4 $2 {is not an option:} gxf4 47. Rxg6+ {(47.Rh3 Nxd3 -+)} Kxg6 48. Bc2 Kh5 {-+ .}) 46... Bxe4+ 47. Bxe4 Qxe4+ 48. Kf1 Kg6 49. Qe3 Qb1+ 50. Qe1 Qc2 {The position is equal, and both sides had to accept this evaluation, but in vain...} 51. Qe2 Qf5+ 52. Qf2 Qe4 53. Qe3 Qc4+ 54. Kg1 g4 55. h3 Qxd5 56. hxg4 Qd1+ 57. Kg2 Qc2+ 58. Kh3 Qb1 59. Kh4 Kg7 60. Rh3 a5 61. Kg3 Qg6 62. Rh4 a4 63. Kh3 c4 64. Kg3 {Still, dynamic equality is in the cards...} Qf6 $2 {A wrong idea.} ({Black had to opt for} 64... Kg8 65. g5 Qb1 {∞ .}) 65. Rh5 $1 Nf7 66. Rf5 Qa1 67. Kg2 $2 ({White could prevail here by} 67. Qf2 $1 Qxa3+ 68. Kg2 Ne5 69. Rg5+ $1 Ng6 70. Qa7+ Kf8 {(70...Kf6 71.Rf5+ Ke6 72.Qf7)} 71. Rxg6 {+- .}) 67... Qd1 68. Qf4 Qe2+ 69. Kg3 Qe6 70. Qd4+ Kg6 71. Rf4 d5 72. Rf5 Qe1+ 73. Kg2 Qe2+ 74. Kg3 Qe1+ 75. Kg2 Qe2+ 76. Qf2 $2 {But the text loses the game!} ({Instead, White could opt for} 76. Rf2 $1 Qe6 77. Rb2 {+- .}) 76... Qxg4+ 0-1

