{Please, here, play the text move Qf3 .} 17. Qf3 (17. Nb3 $1 {was slightly stronger according to Stockfish 17. 17.Nf1 is not bad either.}) 17... Qc6 $1 ({Black has to regroup his pieces to the kingside as well and avoid} 17... cxd4 18. cxd4 Qc6 19. d5 Qd6 20. Nf1 $1 Nxc4 21. Ng3 {± ,}) ({or} 17... exd4 $2 18. e5 $1 Rfe8 19. exf6 {+- ,}) ({or, finally,} 17... Bxc4 $2 18. Nxc4 Nxc4 19. Bh6 {+- .}) 18. d5 Qd6 19. Nf1 $1 {Going for the weak [f5]-square.} Kh8 {Forced.} ({If} 19... Bxc4 $2 20. Ne3 {(20.Bh6? f5 ⩲)} Kh8 21. Bxc4 {+- ,}) ({and if} 19... Nxc4 $2 20. Bxc4 {(20.Bh6 f5 ±)} Bxc4 21. Ne3 {+- .}) 20. Ne3 Bc8 21. Bd2 $16 {The 'bad' bishop is preparing to turn into a monster e1-h4.} Rg8 22. Be1 Rg6 (22... f5 $1 23. exf5 f6 24. Bh4 {seems like a better defence for Black.}) 23. Bh4 $1 Rh6 24. Qf2 {White is rather active, while Black is still searching for a decent plan...} Bd7 25. Rf1 Kg7 $2 {Black cannot hold the game after the text.} ({His only chance was} 25... Nb7 26. Be2 f5 $1 27. exf5 f6 28. Ng4 Qf8 29. Bg3 {± .}) 26. Be2 $1 Rg6 {Stopping [Bg4].} 27. h3 $1 Bxh3 $6 ({Black had to try} 27... Rg8 28. Bh5 Rh6 29. Bg4 Kf8 30. Bxd7 Qxd7 31. Bxf6) {and hope Qxh3? Be7+ +-} 28. Bh5 $1 Bd7 ({White also wins after} 28... Rf8 29. Bxg6 fxg6 30. gxh3 h5 31. Kh2 {+- .}) 29. Bxg6 fxg6 30. Bxf6+ ({And of course, not} 30. Qxf6+ $2 Qxf6 31. Bxf6+ Kg8 {± .}) 30... Kg8 {Material has nearly been restored, and now the weak position of the black king will decide.} 31. Qh4 $1 {Threatens to win with [Be7].} Rf8 32. Rf3 ({Good enough, but} 32. Be7 {was winning:} Rxf1+ 33. Kxf1 Qb8 34. d6 Qe8 35. Nd5 Qf7+ 36. Kg1 Be6 37. Nf6+ Kh8 38. d7 {+- .}) 32... Rf7 33. Qg5 {Winning the important [e5]-pawn - just have a look at the edged [a5]-knight to understand why Black's position collapses...} Qf8 34. Qxe5 Nb7 ({Maybe a bit better was} 34... h6 35. Rf2 Nb7 {, but anyway, Black cannot survive after} 36. Qf4 {.}) 35. Qf4 $1 {White is clearly winning, as the e-pawn is unstoppable.} Nd6 36. e5 Ne8 37. d6 Nxf6 38. exf6 Qe8 39. Nd5 $1 Qe1+ 40. Kh2 Qd1 41. Ne7+ Kh8 42. Rh3 $1 (42. Rh3 {Black resigned:} Qc2 {(42...Bxh3 43.d7! Qxd7 44.Qb8+ +-)} 43. Rg3 $1 a6 44. Qh6 Rxf6 45. Nxg6+ Qxg6 {(45...Rxg6 46.Qf8+ Rg8 47.Qxg8)} 46. Rxg6 Rxg6 47. Qf8+ Rg8 48. Qf6+ Rg7 49. Qd8+ {+- .}) 1-0

