[GameId "2130463736327429"]

{An interesting, 'extremely attractive' and somewhat rare concept is the double exchange sacrifice. When we come to a double exchange sacrifice, then we must realise that this is a complex subject to master, as the chess player is required to overcome the dogmatic rules with which he has been brought up, in particular, the quantitative evaluation of material. But why would somebody think to sacrifice both his rooks? Well, the most usual reason is the attack against the king, but many other pluses can be found, such as controlling important squares, releasing a pawn phalanx, taking over the initiative, etc. But, of course, the sacrificing side gives a lot of material. The Attacking Concept This looks quite easy to understand and practice; the idea of mating is welcomed, and it is easier to explain!} 1. Z0 *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
