[ECO "E41"]
[PlyCount "44"]
[GameId "2130463736343814"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 c5 5. a3 cxd4 6. axb4 dxc3 7. Nf3 cxb2 8. Bxb2 d5 9. c5 b6 10. Bb5+ Bd7 11. Bxd7+ Nfxd7 12. Qc2 Nc6 13. Bxg7 Nxb4 14. Qb1 Rg8 15. c6 Nxc6 16. Qxh7 {White's attack may seem intimidating at first, but it is possible to hold the position. How would you proceed to secure a draw? Tip: The variation is quite long, so take your time to calculate.} Nf6 $1 {More or less forced. But when Geller entered this position, he thought that he had an easy win…} 17. Bxf6 Qxf6 18. Qxg8+ Kd7 19. Ne5+ {The point; Black’s fate seems to be sealed…} Nxe5 (19... Qxe5 $2 20. Qxf7+ Ne7 21. O-O {+- would be rather easy for White.}) 20. Qxa8 Nf3+ $1 {Efim Geller missed the text, not as a move, but as a drawing mechanism.} 21. gxf3 (21. Ke2 Qb2+ 22. Kxf3 Qf6+ {.}) 21... Qxa1+ 22. Ke2 Qa2+ {White has an extra rook, but he cannot avoid the perpetual check on the light squares…} 1/2-1/2

