[GameId "2130463736376586"]

28... Bxa5 ({Black would have no chance to defend after} 28... Rxa5 29. Rxa5 Bxa5 30. Bxh6 Bd8 31. Nxg7 {+- .}) 29. Rxa5 $1 {Once you give the first, the second comes naturally! Well, White just follows his plan: to eliminate the defending [d8]-bishop for the good.} Rxa5 30. Bxh6 $18 {That's the point. While the black pieces are hanging around on the queenside, White is creating a quite dangerous attack on the other side, where his coordinated pieces are bringing Black some hard times. Note how vulnerable the dark squares f6, [g7] are around the black king - the absence of the black dark-squared bishop is instrumental.} Nh7 ({It is probably impossible to find a defence:} 30... gxh6 $6 31. Qf6 {+- .}) ({Or} 30... Rc1+ 31. Nf1 Qc8 32. Nxg7 Bg4 33. hxg4 Nh7 34. Nf5 {+- .}) ({Or} 30... Ra1+ 31. Kh2 $1 Rcc1 32. Nf1 $1 Rxf1 33. Bxf1 Rxf1 34. Nf6+ Kh8 35. Qh5 {+- .}) 31. Nxg7 f5 ({No adequate defence is provided by} 31... f6 32. Qg3 Ng5 (32... Kf7 33. Nf5 {+-}) 33. Nh5 Kh7 34. Bxg5 {+- .}) ({Or} 31... Ra1+ 32. Nf1 f6 (32... f5 33. exf5 Nf6 34. Qg3 Kh8 35. Qg6 {+-}) 33. Qg3 Kh8 34. Nh5 Be8 35. Bg7+ Kg8 36. Bxf6+ Kf8 37. Bg7+ Ke7 {(37...Kf7 38.Bxe5 +-)} 38. Bxe5 dxe5 39. Qg7+ Bf7 40. Qxe5+ Kd8 41. Qxa1 Bxh5 42. Ba6 Qd7 43. Bxc8 Kxc8 44. Qa8+ Kc7 45. Qa5+ Kb7 46. Qxb4+ Ka8 47. Qa5+ Kb7 48. e5 {+- .}) 32. exf5 Qb6 ({Black also loses after} 32... Nf6 33. Nh5 $1 Nxh5 34. Qxh5 Be8 35. Qg5+ Kh8 36. Ne4 {+- .}) ({Or} 32... Kh8 33. Nh5 Be8 34. Bg7+ Kg8 35. Qg3 {+- .}) 33. f6 ({Good enough is} 33. Qg3 Kf7 (33... Kh8 34. Ne6 {+-}) 34. Qg6+ Ke7 35. Qxh7 {+- .}) ({Or even better} 33. Ne6 Ra1+ 34. Kh2 {+- .}) 33... Kh8 34. Nh5 $1 Rg8 35. f7 ({Instead of the text move, more forceful is} 35. Bg7+ Rxg7 36. fxg7+ Kg8 37. Bxh7+ Kxh7 38. g8=Q+ Kxg8 39. Qf6 {+- .}) ({Anyway, Black resigned even after} 35. f7 {. An excellent attacking example by the 10th World Champion.}) 1-0

