19. Kf2 ({Any move by the white king leads to the same result:} 19. Kd2 Qg2+ $1 20. Ke3 (20. Ke1 Nd3+ 21. Kd1 Bg4+ 22. Nf3 Bxf3#) 20... Nd5+ 21. Kd4 Qd2+ {+ -+ .}) ({Or} 19. Kd1 Qc2+ 20. Ke1 Nd3+ 21. Kf1 Qf2# {.}) ({Or, finally,} 19. Kf1 Bh3+ 20. Nxh3 Qg2+ 21. Ke1 Qe2# {. Black again uses the 'attacking units' concept. Here, he is attacking with three coordinated pieces, while White is defending with none!}) {What did Bareev play here?} 19... Qg2+ 20. Ke3 Nd5+ 21. Kd4 Qd2+ 22. Kc5 (22. Kc4 Ne3+ 23. Kb3 Qd5+ 24. Kb4 Nc2+ 25. Ka4 Bd7# {.}) 22... Qe3+ $1 ({It was still possible to go wrong:} 22... b6+ $2 23. Kc6 Ne7+ 24. Kb7 Bxh7 25. Kxa7 {∞ .}) 23. Kc4 (23. Kxd5 Be6# {, or 23.Kb5 Qb6+ 24.Kc4 Ne3 .}) 23... Nb6+ ({After} 23... Nb6+ {, White resigned, as he will be mated:} 24. Kb3 (24. Kb5 c6+ 25. Kb4 Qe4+ 26. Kc5 Qe7+ 27. Kd4 c5#) 24... Qe6+ 25. Kb4 Qc4+ 26. Ka5 Qc5# {.}) 0-1

