[GameId "2130463736470805"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d3 Nc6 4. Nbd2 g6 5. g3 Bg7 6. Bg2 e6 7. O-O Nge7 8. Re1 O-O 9. c3 b6 10. Nf1 Ba6 11. d4 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Ne5 13. Bg5 h6 14. Qa4 Bb7 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Rad1 Rfc8 17. Ne3 Rc5 18. f4 Nc6 19. Nxc6 Bxc6 20. Qc2 Rd8 21. Qe2 Qb7 22. Nc2 b5 23. Rd2 Rc4 24. a3 a5 25. Ne3 {Troianescu had several good moves at his disposal but chose to attack Petrosian's rook instead. How did the young Armenian Grandmaster respond to this mistake?} Rxe4 $1 {An 'obvious' exchange sacrifice. Black's compensation is based on: 1. A central pawn. 2. The bishop pair. 3. Weak light squares around the opponent's king.} 26. Bxe4 Bxe4 27. Nc2 d5 28. Nd4 (28. h3 {would just weaken the white king further:} e5 29. Ne3 exf4 30. gxf4 Rd6 {∓ .}) 28... b4 $1 29. cxb4 axb4 $17 30. a4 $6 ({White should have tried} 30. axb4 Qxb4 31. Nc6 Qb6+ 32. Qf2 Qxc6 33. Rxe4 Bxb2 {∓ .}) 30... Qa7 31. Qf2 Rc8 $1 (31... Qxa4 $2 32. Nxe6 $1 fxe6 33. Rxe4 {⩲ .}) 32. b3 Bf8 33. Nb5 Qa6 34. Qe2 Qb6+ {Editor's Note: To be continued in the next variation .} *

