35. Kf1 Rc3 $1 {Here comes the second one!} 36. Nxc3 ({White is forced to accept the second sacrifice, as alternatives fail to satisfy:} 36. Nd4 Bc5 37. Red1 Bxd4 38. Rxd4 Bf3 39. Qb5 Qxb5+ 40. axb5 Bxd1 41. Rxd1 Rc5 {.}) ({Or} 36. a5 Qxa5 37. Nxc3 bxc3 38. Rd4 Bc5 39. Ra4 Qb6 {∓ .}) 36... bxc3 37. Rc2 (37. Ra2 Qxb3 38. Raa1 c2 {-+ .}) 37... Qxb3 {The black bishop pair and the passed c-pawn dominate the position. White's rooks are passive and not of much help.} 38. Rec1 Bb4 $19 {Black is not in a hurry to win back some material as White lacks sufficient counterplay.} 39. g4 Bxc2 (39... f5 40. gxf5 Bxf5 41. a5 d4 42. a6 d3 {looks even better!}) 40. Rxc2 (40. Qxc2 Qc4+ 41. Kg2 Qxf4 {-+ .}) 40... Qxa4 {Black has won back some material and now is 'just' an exchange down for three healthy pawns. The end is near...} 41. f5 exf5 $1 42. gxf5 g5 43. h4 (43. Ra2 Qc6 44. Ra6 Qc8 $1 45. Rxh6 c2 {-+ .}) 43... Bc5 $1 44. hxg5 (44. Rxc3 $6 Qa1+ 45. Qe1 Qxe1+ 46. Kxe1 Bb4 {-+ .}) 44... Qf4+ 45. Ke1 (45. Kg2 Qxg5+ 46. Kh2 Bd6+ 47. Kh1 Qh4+ 48. Kg1 Qg3+ 49. Kf1 (49. Qg2 d4 $1) 49... Qh3+ 50. Qg2+ Qxg2+ 51. Kxg2 Be5 {-+ .}) 45... Qg3+ 46. Kd1 Qg1+ 47. Qe1 Qxe1+ 48. Kxe1 hxg5 49. Ke2 Bd4 50. Ra2 Kg7 $1 (50... Bf6 $2 51. Kd3 Kg7 52. Rg2 {∓ .}) 51. Kd3 (51. Ra5 c2 52. Kd2 Bc3+ {.}) 51... Be5 $1 52. Ra5 Kf6 53. Rxd5 Kxf5 54. Ke3 f6 55. Rc5 Kg4 56. Rc4+ Kg3 57. Ke4 g4 (57... g4 58. Kf5 Kf3 59. Rxg4 Ke3 {-+ .}) 0-1

