35... Qg6 ({The natural} 35... Bxg2 {loses to} 36. Rxe8+ Rxe8 37. Qxg2 Qd1+ 38. Kh2 g6 39. Qe4 $1 Rc8 40. d5 {+- .}) 36. Rxe4 $1 {Another exchange sacrifice, and again on [e4]-square. Two white bishops and two pawns are worth two black rooks!} Rxe4 37. d5 Rce8 $6 (37... Ree8 38. d6 Qb1+ 39. Kh2 Qd1 40. fxg7 a5 41. Qd2 {+- .}) ({Better is} 37... Rxf4 38. Qxf4 Qd3 {.}) 38. d6 (38. Kh2 {wins as well:} Qf5 39. Bxe4 Qxe4 (39... Rxe4 40. c8=Q+ $1 Qxc8 41. Qg2 g5 42. Qxe4 gxf4 43. d6 {+-}) 40. d6 Qd3 41. fxg7 {+- .}) 38... Re1+ 39. Kh2 Qf5 40. Qg3 g6 41. Qg5 $1 {The most precise. Without the queens, Black is hopeless - no counterplay!} Qxg5 42. Bxg5 Rd1 43. Bc6 Re2+ (43... Rc8 44. Bf4 {+- .}) 44. Kg3 1-0

