1. b3 g6 2. Bb2 Nf6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 d5 5. c4 d4 6. Nf3 c5 7. b4 O-O 8. bxc5 Nc6 9. O-O Nd7 10. d3 Nxc5 11. Nbd2 Re8 12. Ba3 Qa5 13. Qc1 Na4 14. Nb3 Qc7 15. Qc2 Bd7 16. Rae1 Rad8 17. e3 dxe3 18. fxe3 Bf5 19. Nfd4 Nxd4 20. Nxd4 {Stuart Conquest correctly captured the knight. Can you find the sequence that followed?} Rxd4 $1 ({Instead,} 20... Bd7 $6 21. Rb1 b6 22. Nb5 Bxb5 23. Rxb5 {can only be preferable for White. Of course, there is nothing 'strange' with that; such actions happen in a lot of games.}) 21. exd4 ({White had to accept the sacrifice, as after} 21. Qxa4 Qd7 $1 22. Qxa7 (22. Qxd7 $2 Rxd7 23. d4 Bd3 24. Rf2 e5 25. dxe5 Bxc4 {∓}) 22... Rxd3 23. Bb4 Rc8 24. a3 Rxc4 25. Qxb7 Qxb7 26. Bxb7 Rc7 {, Black's stands slightly better due to White's shattered pawn structure.}) 21... Bxd4+ 22. Kh1 Nc5 {A very interesting and about forced exchange sacrifice for purely positional compensation occupation of important central squares and better pawn structure.} 23. Rd1 ({White should have complicated matters further with} 23. Bxc5 $1 Bxc5 24. Be4 Bh3 25. Bg2 (25. Rf3 Qa5 $1 26. Rb1 b6 {∓}) 25... Bc8 $1 (25... Bf5) 26. Bd5 Rf8 27. Qb2 e6 28. Be4 Rd8 {∞ .}) 23... Rd8 24. Qe2 b6 *

