1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bg2 Be6 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O Nb6 8. d3 Be7 9. a3 a5 10. Be3 O-O 11. Na4 Nxa4 12. Qxa4 Bd5 13. Rfc1 Re8 14. Rc2 Bf8 15. Rac1 Nb8 {Black is ready to ease the pressure down the c-file by playing ...[c6]. But White's forces are well placed and ready to act.} 16. Rxc7 $1 {White voluntarily traps his rook, but he doesn't really care, as he wants to sacrifice it anyway!} Bc6 17. R1xc6 $1 bxc6 ({There is not much difference after} 17... Nxc6 {, as} 18. Rxf7 $1 {is still possible.}) 18. Rxf7 $1 {Here comes the second sacrifice again! White's play on the light squares in this game is impressive. To be continued in the following variation.} *

