18... h6 ({Accepting the second sacrifice leads to disaster anyway:} 18... Kxf7 19. Qc4+ Kg6 20. Qg4+ Kf7 21. Ng5+ {+- . With his last move, Black tried to prevent an eventual [Ng5], but at the same time, created more weaknesses on the light squares around his king.}) {How responded Botvinnik in this position?} 19. Rb7 Qc8 ({Black decided to fall like a brave man! The other option with} 19... Qf6 20. Qc4+ Qe6 21. Nxe5 Qxc4 22. Nxc4 {+- promised him a slow and painful death!}) 20. Qc4+ Kh8 21. Nh4 $1 {The [b7]-rook is irrelevant. The coordination of White's queen and three minor pieces is impressive, especially on the light squares around the black king.} Qxb7 22. Ng6+ Kh7 23. Be4 $1 {There is no defence for Black any more.} Bd6 24. Nxe5+ g6 (24... Kh8 25. Nf7+ Kg8 26. Nxd6+ {.}) 25. Bxg6+ Kg7 26. Bxh6+ $1 (26. Bxh6+ {, the last detail! Black resigned due to} Kxh6 27. Qh4+ Kg7 28. Qh7+ {+- .}) 1-0

