1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e6 5. g3 Nc6 6. Bg2 Bc5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. Nc3 O-O 9. O-O d6 10. Bf4 Nh5 11. e3 Nxf4 12. exf4 Bd7 13. Qd2 Qb8 14. Rfe1 g6 15. h4 a6 16. h5 b5 17. hxg6 hxg6 18. Nc5 dxc5 19. Qxd7 Rc8 {Topalov, in a losing position, supported his knight, which is perfectly logical and indeed the best move. How did Karpov respond?} 20. Rxe6 $1 {A nice exchange sacrifice and the point of White's previous moves ( 20.Bxc6? Ra7 ) .} Ra7 (20... fxe6 21. Bxc6 Ra7 22. Qxe6+ Kg7 23. Be4 Bf6 24. Qg4 {+- .}) 21. Rxg6+ $1 {The rook persists in its 'suicidal' ways! Black has no choice:} Kf8 ({Or} 21... Kh7 22. Qh3+ Kxg6 23. Be4+ f5 (23... Kg7 24. Qh7+ Kf6 25. Qh6#) 24. Qxf5+ Kg7 25. Qh7+ Kf8 26. Qh6+ Ke8 27. Bxc6+ {+- .}) 22. Qh3 fxg6 23. Qh8+ Kf7 24. Bd5# *

