21... fxg6 ({Black has no choice:} 21... Kf8 22. Qh3 fxg6 23. Qh8+ Kf7 24. Bd5# {.}) ({Or} 21... Kh7 22. Qh3+ Kxg6 23. Be4+ f5 (23... Kg7 24. Qh7+ Kf6 25. Qh6#) 24. Qxf5+ Kg7 25. Qh7+ Kf8 26. Qh6+ Ke8 27. Bxc6+ {+- .}) 22. Qe6+ Kg7 23. Bxc6 $18 {With the help of the exchange sacrifice, White succeeded in breaking down the defence of the black king and achieving active play for his pieces. One must also add to this the two pawns he collected on the way.} Rd8 (23... Bf6 24. Be4 Rf8 25. Nd5 {± .}) 24. cxb5 Bf6 ({Alternatives are not helpful:} 24... Qd6 25. Qxd6 Bxd6 26. b6 Re7 27. Rd1 {+- , or 24...axb5 25.Nxb5 +- .}) 25. Ne4 Bd4 (25... Bxb2 26. Rb1 Bd4 27. b6 Rf7 28. Ng5 {+- .}) 26. bxa6 Qb6 ({Unfortunately for Black,} 26... Rxa6 {would not save him:} 27. Qe7+ Kh8 {(27...Kg8 28.Bd7 +-)} 28. Ng5 Ra7 29. Nf7+ Kg7 30. Qxd8 Qxb2 31. Qh8+ Kxf7 32. Bd5+ Ke7 33. Re1+ Kd6 34. Qd8+ Rd7 35. Re6+ Kxd5 36. Qxd7+ {+- .}) 27. Rd1 *

