1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. c3 d6 8. d4 Bb6 9. Be3 O-O 10. Nbd2 Bb7 11. Re1 exd4 12. cxd4 Nb4 13. Qe2 c5 14. a3 Nc6 15. d5 Ne7 16. h3 Re8 17. Bc2 Ng6 18. b3 Ba5 19. Rab1 Bc3 20. Rec1 b4 21. a4 a5 22. Bd3 h6 23. Qd1 Ba6 24. Bc2 Ra7 25. Kh2 Rae7 26. g4 {The 'Minister of Defense' erred with this pawn push. Can you find one of the ways to punish it?} Nxe4 $1 (26... Bxd2 27. Nxd2 Nxd5 $1 28. exd5 Rxe3 29. fxe3 Rxe3 {seems to work for Black, and if} 30. Nc4 {(preventing ...[Re2]+)} Bxc4 31. bxc4 Qh4 32. Qf1 Ne5 33. Qg2 Nf3+ 34. Kh1 Nd4 35. Kh2 Re2 {would have been a nice way of converting the advantage, but it is understandable that one wouldn't consider such a rook sacrifice in a dominant position.}) 27. Nxe4 Rxe4 28. Bxe4 Rxe4 {It would be fair to assess the situation as generally hopeless for White, who has many weak points, while Black is extremely active.} *

