29. Qc2 Qe7 30. Rg1 ({Karjakin could have prolonged the game by playing a bad position, being a pawn down after} 30. Re1 Bxe1 31. Rxe1 Qe8 {.}) 30... Rxe3 $1 {Here the second comes!} 31. fxe3 Qxe3 {After Black's sacrifice of the second exchange, White is unable to defend his destroyed position.} 32. Rbf1 (32. Rg3 {is the best defense.}) 32... Be2 33. Qf5 Bd3 $1 34. Qd7 Be5+ 35. Kh1 ({There is no salvation:} 35. Nxe5 Qxe5+ 36. Kh1 Qe4+ 37. Kh2 Qe2+ 38. Kg3 (38. Kh1 Be4+ {+ -+}) 38... Qe5+ 39. Kg2 Nh4+ {+ -+ .}) 35... Be4 36. Qe8+ Nf8 (36... Nf8 {and White resigned. After} 37. Kg2 {, Black mates:} Qe2+ 38. Rf2 Bxf3# {.}) 0-1

