25... Ra7 ({Or} 25... Rb8 26. Ba4 {and Black has to resign. 26.Rxd5 Qxf2+ 27.Qxf2 Bxf2+ 28.Kxf2 cxd5 29.Ba4+ Rb5 30.Ke3 Rxf7 31.Bxb5+ axb5 32.exf7+ Kxf7 33.Kd4 Ke6 34.Bd2 +- is equally good.}) ({Editor's Note: the engine advises ...Qxf2+ now,} 25... Qxf2+ 26. Kh1 Rxf7 {, entering in tactical subtleties.}) 26. Rxd5 $1 {A second exchange sacrifice on the same square! But this time, this sacrifice must be considered the introduction to a winning combination and not a positional one, as was the case on the 17th move.} Qxf2+ (26... Raxf7 27. exf7+ Rxf7 28. Rxc5 Rxf3 29. Re5+ {+- , or 26...cxd5 27.Ba4+ +- .}) 27. Qxf2 Bxf2+ 28. Kh1 $1 ({If} 28. Kxf2 Rfxf7+ 29. exf7+ Rxf7+ 30. Rf5 {.}) 28... Bb6 (28... Rd7 29. Rxd7 {(( 29...Rxf7 30.Rd8# ))} c3 30. Nd6#) 29. Nd6# {I was so dizzy and in a heavy time trouble that I didn't feel that this was possible. In those times when I had a quarrel with my girlfriend, she simply upset me by just shouting to me, 'Trindade'!} 1-0

