1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 d5 4. exd5 exd5 5. d4 Nc6 6. Bg2 Nf6 7. O-O Be7 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. a3 O-O 10. Nc3 Re8 11. b4 d4 12. Na4 Bf8 13. c4 dxc3 14. Nxc3 Bg4 15. Be3 Qc8 16. Qb3 Be6 17. Qb2 Bh3 18. Rfd1 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 Qf5 20. h3 Rac8 21. Qb3 Rxe3 {An interesting exchange sacrifice, aiming to weaken the white king.} 22. fxe3 Ne5 23. Nxe5 Qxe5 24. Rac1 Qxe3 25. Qb2 Nh5 26. Ne2 Re8 27. Rd2 Qe4+ 28. Kh2 g6 {Black's position is quite solid, so he further improves it!} 29. Rf1 Bh6 30. Rc2 Qd3 $1 31. Qa2 $2 (31. Rg1 {was the only move:} Ng7 $1 32. Rg2 Nf5 {∞ .}) 31... Rxe2+ $1 {Here comes the second!} 32. Rxe2 Qxg3+ 33. Kh1 Qxh3+ 34. Kg1 Qg3+ 35. Kh1 Qh3+ 36. Kg1 Be3+ $2 ({Natural, but much stronger was} 36... Qg4+ $1 37. Kh2 Bf4+ 38. Rxf4 Qxf4+ 39. Kg2 Qg3+ 40. Kf1 Nf4 {∓ .}) 37. Rxe3 {The third!} Qxe3+ 38. Qf2 Qg5+ 39. Kh2 Qe7 40. Qxa7 Qe5+ 41. Kg1 Nf4 42. Rxf4 $1 {And the fourth!} Qxf4 43. Qxb7 {Black remained an extra pawn up, but in queens' endings, the importance of passed pawns is highly appreciated.} h5 44. b5 h4 45. b6 Qe3+ 46. Kh2 Qf2+ 47. Kh1 Qf1+ 48. Kh2 1/2-1/2

