1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. d4 Nd6 6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. dxe5 Nf5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. Nc3 Bd7 10. b3 b6 11. Bb2 Kc8 12. Rad1 h5 13. Ne2 Be7 14. Nf4 Be8 15. g3 Kb7 16. h4 c5 17. c4 Bc6 18. Ng5 Bxg5 19. hxg5 h4 20. g4 h3 21. Kh2 Rh4 22. f3 Ne3 23. Rde1 Ng2 24. Kg3 Nxe1 25. Rxe1 h2 26. Kxh4 Bxf3 27. e6 fxe6 28. Bxg7 e5 29. Kg3 h1=Q 30. Rxh1 Bxh1 31. Bxe5 Be4 32. Nd5 Bb1 33. a3 Rg8 34. Bf6 Ba2 35. Ne7 Re8 36. b4 cxb4 37. axb4 Bxc4 38. g6 a5 39. bxa5 bxa5 40. Nf5 a4 41. Bb2 Re2 42. Bf6 a3 43. g7 a2 44. g5 Re1 45. Nh6 a1=Q 46. Bxa1 Rxa1 47. g8=Q Bxg8 48. Nxg8 c5 49. Ne7 c4 50. Nf5 c3 51. Ne3 Rg1+ 52. Kf4 Kc6 53. Kf5 Kd6 54. g6 Rg3 55. Nc2 Rg2 56. Ne3 Rf2+ 57. Ke4 $6 {A critical game from the match Netherlands-Russia in the European Team Championship 2013. At this moment Russia was leading 2-1.} c2 {The obvious ...[c2] was curtains and a 2-2 final result.} (57... Ke6 $4 {was played in the game, leading to a drawish position} 58. g7 Kf7 59. Kd3 {. You can train this variation with White here.}) 58. Nxc2 Rxc2 59. g7 Rg2 $19 {Editor's Note: It's difficult to see what stopped Robin Van Kampen from playing ...[c2].} *

