1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 Nxd4 7. Qxd4 d6 8. Be3 Bg7 9. Be2 O-O 10. Qd2 Qa5 11. f3 Be6 12. b3 Rfc8 13. Rc1 a6 14. Na4 Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nd7 16. g4 f5 17. exf5 gxf5 18. h3 Rf8 19. f4 Rad8 20. Nc3 {A key position in the 'Sicilian Defence – Accelerated Dragon Variation' has been reached. The funny thing is that Gadir Guseinov had reached exactly this position precisely four times as Black. So, it was possible that White had come with some preparation, but it was not to be. Black played a nice exchange sacrifice.} d5 $1 21. cxd5 Nf6 (21... Bxd5 {is as good.}) 22. Bb6 Nxd5 $1 23. Bxd8 Rxd8 (23... Bxc3+ {is as good} 24. Rxc3 Nxc3) 24. Nxd5 Bxd5 25. Rh2 ({Some alternatives are} 25. Ke3 Bxh1 26. Rxh1 Bd4+ 27. Kf3 Bc5 28. gxf5 {(28.Rd1 Rxd1 29.Bxd1 ½-½ A. Saric – G. Guseinov, Tallinn 2019. )} Kg7 29. Rc1 b6 30. a4 {(30.Rc2 a5 31.Bc4 Kf6 32.Rg2 Rd4 33.Rg8 Bd6 34.Rf8+ Kg7 35.Rg8+ Kf6 36.Rf8+ Kg7 37.Rf7+ Kh6 38.Ke3 Rxf4 39.Bd3 Rh4 40.f6 Bc5+ 41.Ke2 exf6 42.Rxh7+ Kg5 43.Rxh4 ½-½ A. Filippov – G. Guseinov, Nakhchivan 2012. )} a5 31. Rd1 Rxd1 32. Bxd1 {½-½ R. Mamedov – G. Guseinov, Baku 2012,}) ({or} 25. Rhg1 Bxb3+ 26. Ke1 Bxa2 27. Rc7 Kf8 28. Rg3 b5 29. Re3 Re8 30. Ra3 Bf7 31. Rxa6 fxg4 32. hxg4 b4 33. g5 Bd4 34. Bc4 Bg6 35. Ke2 Rd8 36. Rb7 Bh5+ 37. Kf1 Be3 38. Ra5 Bg4 39. Rd5 Rc8 40. Rxb4 Be6 41. Ke2 Bxd5 42. Bxd5 Bc5 {½-½ V. Kovalev – G. Guseinov, Moscow 2013.}) 25... Bxb3+ $1 26. Ke1 Bxa2 27. Bxa6 $1 bxa6 28. Rxa2 Rd4 $10 {White is an exchange up but has no chance of winning as the black bishop has a strong post on [f6]. A nice exchange sacrifice, made for defensive purposes.} 29. gxf5 (29. Rf2 Rd3 30. Rh2 Rd4 31. gxf5 Rxf4 32. Rf2 Ra4 {L. Miknevicius – L. Koehn, Prague 2016.}) 29... Rxf4 30. Rc5 Rf3 31. h4 Rh3 32. Ra4 Bf6 33. Rcc4 Kg7 34. Kf2 Kh6 35. Kg2 Rb3 36. Rxa6 Kh5 37. Raa4 Rb2+ 38. Kf3 Rb3+ 39. Kg2 Rb2+ 40. Kf3 Rb3+ 41. Ke2 Rb2+ 42. Ke3 Rh2 43. Rg4 Bxh4 44. Kf3 {½-½ P. Smirnov – G. Guseinov, Khanty-Mansiysk 2011.} 1/2-1/2

