[PlyCount "70"]
[GameId "2130463736786236"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Qb3 dxc4 6. Qxc4 O-O 7. e4 a6 8. Be2 b5 9. Qb3 c5 10. dxc5 Bb7 11. e5 Nfd7 12. Be3 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Rd1 Qc7 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. Qxd5 Nc6 17. Bf3 Rac8 18. Qxc6 Qxc6 19. Bxc6 Rxc6 20. Rd2 f5 21. f4 Bf6 22. Ke2 Kf7 23. Rc1 Rfc8 24. Kf3 a5 25. Rcc2 Ke8 26. Rd3 Rd8 27. Rb3 Rb8 28. Ra3 a4 29. b3 Ra8 30. bxa4 b4 31. Rb3 Rxa4 32. Rc4 Rxa2 33. Rcxb4 {Thanks to the outside passed pawn on [c5], White has a small edge. Black has to be careful about it. Black's next move was very accurate and White had no scope for victory after that.} Rc2 $1 34. Rb6 R6xc5 (34... Rc7 {was fine as well, but the text is clearer.}) 35. Bxc5 Rxc5 $10 {[%cal Ge8f7,Gh7h6,Gh6h5,Gc5c2,Gc2c1] With this nice defensive exchange sacrifice, Black secures the draw, and White has no chances to win as the weakness of the [e7]-pawn is firmly defended by the [f6]-bishop.} 1/2-1/2

