1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Qc7 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Be2 Bd7 9. O-O Nge7 10. a4 Na5 11. Re1 cxd4 12. cxd4 Nc4 13. Bd3 h6 14. Nd2 Nxd2 15. Bxd2 Nc6 16. Qg4 g6 17. Re3 O-O-O 18. Rg3 Kb8 19. Rf3 f5 20. exf6 e5 21. Qg3 Nxd4 22. Re3 e4 {Although in most sources this position is given as a tactical exercise, the reality is that this is a great exchange sacrifice example!} 23. Rxe4 $1 Qxg3 24. Rxd4 $1 {The black queen cannot escape.} Qc7 {After the alternative ...[Qc7], White wins material:} 25. Bf4 Rhf8 26. Bxc7+ Kxc7 27. Rh4 {[%csl Rh6,Rg6] ( 27.Rxd5? doesn't weaken Black's kindside 27...Rxf6 . )} (27. Rh4 h5 28. Bxg6 Rxf6 29. Bd3) *

[Event "The Strategy Instructors Volume 3: The Exchange Sacrifice"]
