[GameId "2130463736847682"]

28... Rde8 29. f7 ({Editor's Note:: engines would prefer to control the promotion square with} 29. Bb4 {, threaten a double attack with 29.Bc3 or play the simple 29.f3 .}) 29... Re7 (29... Ref8 $4 {is bad} 30. Bg6 Rhg8 {.}) 30. f8=Q+ {Clearing up.} ({Note from Chessable: better of as good are: • the threats} 30. h3 {, 30.f3 and 30.Bc3 ; • the solidification 30.Bg6 ; or, • any promotion, like 30.f8=N .}) 30... Rxf8 31. Bb4 Rff7 32. Bxe7 $18 {White won the exchange back and remained with an extra pawn and of course, a won position.} Rxe7 33. f3 Bd7 34. a5 Kc7 35. Kf2 Rf7 36. Ke3 Kd6 37. g3 Kc5 38. f4 Bg4 39. Rb1 Re7+ 40. Kd2 b6 41. axb6 axb6 42. h3 $1 Bd7 (42... Bxh3 43. Rh1 Bg4 44. Rxh6 Bf3 45. Rg6 {+- .}) 43. g4 d4 44. f5 Re3 45. f6 $1 Rf3 (45... Rxh3 46. f7 Rf3 47. Rf1 {+- .}) 46. Rf1 $1 Rxf1 47. Bxf1 Be6 (47... Be6 {Black resigned, as he noticed the coming} 48. h4 Kd6 49. g5 hxg5 50. hxg5 Ke5 {(50...Bf7 51.Bd3 +-)} 51. Bd3 Bg8 52. Bg6 Ke6 53. Kd3 {+- .}) 1-0

