[PlyCount "38"]
[GameId "2130463736995146"]

23... Bd2 $2 {With the understandable desire to control square [c1]. However, instead of this, Black should have tried to create counterplay, since after the game move, White's rook can be transferred on the c-file anyway.} (23... Bxh4 {was the only chance:} 24. Rc1 Rf8 $1 {(24...Kf7? 25.b7 Rf8 (25...Ke6 26.Nc7+ Ke7 27.Nxe8 Rxe8 28.Rc8 +-) 26.g3 Bg5 27.Rc8 Ke6 (27...Bd2 28.Nb6 Ke7 29.Rxf8 Rxf8 30.Nc8+ +-) 28.Nb6 +-)} 25. g3 Bg5 26. Rc6 {(26.Rc7?! e3 27.fxe3 Rxb6 ⩱)} Kf7 27. Rxd6 {(27.b7 Ke6 28.Nb6 e3 ∞)} Rfd8 28. Rc6 e3 29. fxe3 Rxd5 30. Bc4 Bxe3+ 31. Kg2 Rxb6 32. Bxd5+ Ke7 {.}) 24. b7 Kf7 25. Rd1 Bh6 26. Nb4 $6 {An inaccuracy.} ({Good was} 26. b3 g6 27. g4 Bf4 28. b4 {+- .}) 26... Ke7 27. Nd5+ Kf7 $2 ({Black repeats the position; he should have gone for} 27... Kf8 $1 28. Re1 Red8 29. Rxe4 Rd7 30. Rb4 Kf7 31. Rb5 {± .}) 28. g4 $6 (28. b3 $1 {, again, was best - see above.}) 28... Bf4 29. Re1 g5 (29... Red8 $1 {is a fair try:} 30. Rxe4 g5 31. hxg5 Bxg5 32. Kf1 Rd7 33. Rb4 {⩲ .}) 30. Re2 $1 {If not from [c1], then from [c2]! Taking pawn [e4] means in some variations helping Black including his bishop into the defence:} (30. Rxe4 Red8 31. Nb4 d5 32. Re2 gxh4 33. Rc2 e4 {∞ .}) (30. h5 {looks also strong, preventing Black's 30...gxh4, which is possible in the game.}) 30... Red8 $2 ({There is no clear win for White after} 30... gxh4 $1 31. Rc2 {( White can play 31.Kg2 of course, but then it is clear that Black had to insert 30...[gxh4] )} h3 32. Rc7+ {( or 32.Rc8 h5 ∞)} Kg6 33. Ne7+ Kg5 34. Nc6 e3 $1 35. fxe3 Bxe3+ 36. Kh2 Kh4 $1 {(36...Kxg4? 37.Nxb8 Rxb8 38.Rc8 Ba7 39.b4! d5 40.b5 +-)} 37. Nxb8 Rxb8 38. Rc8 {(38.Rxh7+ Kxg4=)} Ba7 39. b4 e4 40. b5 d5 41. Kh1 $1 {(41.b6? Bxb6 -+)} e3 42. b6 e2 43. Bxe2 Rxb7 44. bxa7 Rxa7 {.}) 31. Nb4 $1 d5 (31... gxh4 {is losing to} 32. Nc6 h3 33. Nxd8+ Rxd8 34. Rc2 {+- ,}) ({as well as} 31... Rd7 32. Nc6 Rdxb7 33. Bxb7 Rxb7 34. Nd8+ {+- .}) 32. Nc6 Rg8 33. Nxb8 Rxb8 34. h5 $1 {Black cannot keep his h-pawn alive, which means that White will create a second passed pawn. Meaning he wins easily.} Ke7 35. Kf1 d4 36. Rc2 e3 37. fxe3 dxe3 (37... Bxe3 38. Rc8 {+- .}) 38. Rc7+ Kf6 39. Rxh7 e4 40. Bc4 Rd8 41. Rf7+ Ke5 42. Rd7 $1 1-0

