41... Kd7 42. Ke3 $1 {The priority must be to organise the advancement of White's chief asset while avoiding the black rooks becoming active.} Kd6 43. h6 $1 (43. Nc6 $2 Rf7 $1 {(43...Rxc6? 44.dxc6 b5 45.axb5 axb5 46.Rf1 ±)} 44. Rxc4 b5 45. axb5 axb5 46. Rb4 Rf1 {∞}) (43. Nf3 $2 b5 44. axb5 axb5 45. Kd4 Rf7 46. Nxg5 Rf2 {∞}) 43... Rec8 44. Ne6 Re7 45. Nxg5 $18 {This is how the game ended: 42.Nf5? Rc5! 43.Ng7 Re7 44.Ne6 Rxe6! 45.dxe6+ . The players agreed to a draw as after 45...Kxe6 , there is no question of a White's advantage any more. 42.Nc6? was also insufficient: 42...b5 43.axb5 axb5 44.e5 Rxc6 45.dxc6+ Kxc6 46.Ke4 Rf8! and again Black has become active.} 1/2-1/2

