[White "8) The Passive Exchange Sacrifice"]
[Black "Reshevsky vs. Petrosian #2"]
[Result "1/2-1/2"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "3rq1k1/4n1pp/4p1b1/pp2P3/P1pP1Q2/2P1R3/1B4PP/4R1K1 w - - 0 28"]
[PlyCount "27"]
[GameId "2130463737072978"]

28. Qf1 (28. Qf2 $2 Nd5 29. Rf3 b4 {∓ would be ideal for Black.}) 28... Nd5 29. Rf3 Bd3 30. Rxd3 $1 {White correctly returns the exchange, as any queen move would have allowed 30...b4.} cxd3 31. Qxd3 b4 $1 32. cxb4 (32. c4 $6 {fails to} Nb6 33. Rc1 $6 {(33.d5! exd5 34.c5 Nc4 35.Bd4 Qe6 ⩱)} Nxa4 34. Ba1 Qc6 {∓ .}) 32... axb4 ({Also good was} 32... Nxb4 33. Qb5 {(33.Qb3 Nd5 ⩱)} Qxb5 34. axb5 Nd3 35. Rb1 $1 Nxb2 36. Rxb2 Rxd4 37. b6 Rd8 38. Kf2 a4 {.}) 33. a5 Ra8 34. Ra1 {[%cal Ge8c6]} Qc6 {Black is now only a pawn down, but his superior minor piece provides more than enough compensation.} 35. Bc1 Qc7 ({Now, another exchange sacrifice with} 35... Rxa5 $2 36. Rxa5 Qxc1+ 37. Qf1 Qe3+ 38. Kh1 h6 39. Ra8+ Kh7 40. Qb1+ g6 41. Ra7+ Kh8 42. h3 {+- simply fails!}) 36. a6 Qb6 37. Bd2 b3 38. Qc4 h6 39. h3 b2 40. Rb1 Kh8 41. Be1 {There is nothing left to do for both sides. I am sure that Black would have lost the game if he had not found the necessary 25...[Re6]!.} 1/2-1/2

