[PlyCount "10"]
[GameId "2130463737109847"]

25. Be7 ({White's hand is forced, as after} 25. dxe6 fxe6 26. Nd2 {(26.Be7?! Bxc6 ∓)} Nb8 {, Black has nothing to complain of.}) 25... f5 26. Bxf8 Nxf8 (26... Rxf8 {(was possible. Let's see what Black has achieved with the exchange sacrifice he opted for: 1. A strong pawn centre. 2. No active play for White no open files for the rooks. 3. Dark squares control. 4. Excellent outpost on [c5]-square. On the contrary, White's [c6]-square outpost is really irrelevant, as the [c6]-knight might be out of play in reality.)}) 27. Be2 Bh6 28. Rc2 Bc8 29. Nc3 Nfd7 {[%cal Gd7f6] Black is regrouping his pieces to better squares or diagonals. On the contrary, White can only wait...} *

