[PlyCount "15"]
[GameId "2130463737122137"]

32. Rce2 ({The other option was} 32. f3 Bf5 33. Rb2 Bg5 34. g4 fxg3 35. hxg3 h5 {, when Black will organise an assault on the white king. Note how the white rooks are just hanging around.}) 32... Rf8 $6 (32... Bf5 {∞ was the correct follow-up.}) 33. Na4 {White grabbed his best chance: to exchange the strong [c5]-knight.} ({But it must be noted that} 33. Nxe5 {was quite interesting:} dxe5 34. d6 Qg7 35. Rxe5 {∞ .}) 33... Nxa4 34. Qxa4 Nd7 ({Black would love to play} 34... Bg5 $2 {first, but this fails to} 35. c5 $1 {and White is on the top:} bxc5 36. Rb2 {± .}) 35. Ne7+ {Also exchanging the 'useless' [c6]-knight.} Kh8 36. Nxc8 Qxc8 37. Qa3 $2 (37. f3 Nc5 38. Qc2 Bg7 39. Rd1 {∞ would have preserved the balance.}) 37... Nc5 $2 ({Black missed a good chance with} 37... f3 $1 38. gxf3 Nc5 39. Bg2 Bf4 {∓ , when the white rooks are doing nothing, but the black minor pieces do!}) 38. Qf3 $1 Qf5 39. h3 {Although Black made some inaccuracies, there was no way for White to exploit his extra exchange, as Black's remaining pieces are well-placed. The opponents agreed to a draw in this approximately equal position.} 1/2-1/2

