28. Nxc7 Nxc7 $6 (28... Kxc7 {is a far better move. After} 29. cxd4 Bb4+ 30. Kd1 {(30.Bd2 Nxd4 31.Qxc4+ Bc5= ∞)} Ne5 $1 31. Rf1 {(31.dxe5 Qd7+ 32.Bd2 Rd8 33.Nc3 Nd4 34.e6! Nxe6= ∞)} Rf8 {∞ , Black should be happy with his position. As long as both kings are exposed, no side can feel safe...}) 29. cxd4 (29. Nxd4 {was interesting:} Bc5+ 30. Qe2 Bxd4 31. cxd4 Qf7 32. Rf1 Qd5 {∞ .}) 29... Qf7 $6 {After a very good (although forced!) exchange sacrifice, Black slips a bit.} ({Unclear was the 'obvious'} 29... Bb4+ 30. Bd2 Nd5 $1 {.}) 30. b3 $6 (30. Bd2 $1 Rf8 31. Rc1 Qf2+ 32. Kd1 Qxg2 33. Re1 Qg4 34. Qxc4 Bd6 {was still messy, but White would have made progress.}) 30... Rf8 31. bxc4 Qf2+ $6 ({Black again missed the bishop's check:} 31... Bb4+ $1 32. Rxb4 {(32.Bd2? Qf2+ 33.Kd1 Qf1+ 34.Rxf1 Rxf1 + -+) (32.Nc3? Qxc4 33.Bd2 Qxd4 -+)} Qf2+ 33. Kd1 Qxg2 34. Rg1 {(34.Re1 axb4 ∞)} Rf1+ 35. Rxf1 Qxf1+ 36. Kd2 axb4 {, with equal chances.}) 32. Kd1 Qxg2 33. Re1 Na6 34. Rb3 Nb4 35. Qg6 Rf6 36. Qg8+ Kc7 37. Re3 $1 Bd6 $6 ({It seems that} 37... Bf8 {was a bit better again. After} 38. Bd2 Qg4 {, Black is still in the game and quite alive!}) 38. Bd2 Bf4 {Black decided to sac another exchange, a concept that he prepared with his previous move and it is probably his best chance.} (38... Qg4 {loses to} 39. Qa8 {.}) 39. Nxf4 Rxf4 40. R3e2 Qf3 {The game was agreed drawn ?!.} (40... Qf3 {White should be better after} 41. Bxf4+ gxf4 42. Qg6 Qb3+ 43. Rc2 Qf3+ 44. Ree2 {, but of course his king would be very exposed as well. Nevertheless, he could try... An interesting exchange sacrifice, which is balanced in between the active and the passive concept!}) 1/2-1/2

