1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 9. b4 a5 10. Ba3 axb4 11. Bxb4 Nd7 12. a4 Bh6 13. a5 f5 14. Bd3 Kh8 15. Re1 Nf6 16. c5 fxe4 17. cxd6 cxd6 18. Nxe4 Nxe4 19. Bxe4 Bf5 20. Qd3 Qd7 21. Qa3 Bxe4 22. Rxe4 Nf5 23. g4 {A complicated position, where Black has to seek for activity.} Ne3 $2 {An inspired but wrong exchange sacrifice.} ({The objective} 23... Qf7 $1 24. gxf5 Qxf5 25. Qd3 Qxf3 26. Qxf3 Rxf3 27. Bxd6 Rd3 $1 28. Bxe5+ Kg8 29. d6 Bf8 30. Rb4 Bxd6 31. Bxd6 Rxd6 32. Rxb7 Raa6 {should hold for Black.}) {How do you respond to this attempt?} 24. Nxe5 $1 {White accepts the sacrifice, which is the correct decision on principle.} ({Instead, he couldn't opt for} 24. fxe3 $2 Rxf3 25. Bxd6 Kg8 $1 {( Or 25...Bxe3+? 26.Kg2 (26.Rxe3? Rxe3 27.Qxe3 Qxd6 with chances for both sides. ) 26...Bd4 27.Qxf3 Qxd6 28.Rf1 Qxd5 29.h4 ±)} 26. Bc5 Qb5 {-+ .}) ({Naturally, it was bad to play} 24. Rxe3 $2 Bxe3 25. Qxe3 Qxg4+ {+ -+ .}) 24... dxe5 25. Bxf8 Rxf8 26. Rxe3 $1 {[%cal Rd7g4]} ({After the logical sequence} 26. fxe3 $6 Qxd5 27. Qb4 {(27.Qa4 Qd2= ∞ , ) ( or 27.Ra4? Qf3 -+)} Qf7 $1 {(27...Qd3? 28.Re1 Qc2 29.Rf1 +-)} 28. Qb2 Qf3 29. Qg2 Bxe3+ 30. Kh1 Bd4 {, the position is approximately balanced.}) *

