[GameId "2130463737314664"]

31. Ra4 $2 {Winning a second pawn, but allowing Black to get extremely active.} ({He should have opted for} 31. Bc4 $1 Bxc4 32. Nxc4 Ree7 33. Nxa5 Rcd7 34. Rxd7 Rxd7 35. Kc3 f5 $1 36. b4 fxe4 37. fxe4 Kf6 38. a4 Ke5 39. b5 cxb5 40. axb5 Kxe4 41. Kc4 {.}) 31... f5 $1 32. Kd2 (32. Rxa5 $6 {loses to} fxe4 33. fxe4 Bf5 {-+ .}) 32... fxe4 33. fxe4 Rce7 $1 34. Bf3 $2 (34. Rxa5 $2 Bf5 $1 {is also bad for White,}) ({but he should have continued with} 34. Bd3 $1 Rf8 $1 35. Ke3 Ref7 36. Rd4 $1 {(36.Rxa5? Rf2 -+)} h4 37. h3 g5 {∓ . One has to admit though that the black rooks have now become very active.}) 34... g5 $1 35. Bxh5 Rh8 36. g4 ({Black wins after} 36. Bf3 g4 {and 37...Rxh2. But now the [h5]-bishop is cut-off from the remaining white army.}) 36... Rf8 $1 37. Ke3 Rf1 38. Kd4 Rf4 39. Kd3 Rf3+ 40. Kd4 Rf4 41. Kd3 {White has made quite a good effort to be active and give his rooks the maximum capacity to create counterplay via open files. And that’s the required strategy in such cases!} Kf6 $1 {The timely activation of the black king ensures victory.} 42. Rxa5 Ke5 43. Kc3 ({Or} 43. Ra4 Rf3+ $1 {, with the idea of ...[Rh3] and ...[Kf4].}) 43... Rxe4 44. Ra7 Bxg4 45. Bxg4 Rxg4 {Now, Black will prevail, as he is extremely active.} 46. Nc4+ Kd5 47. Kb4 ({The result wouldn't be changed after} 47. Rxb7 Rxb7 48. Ne3+ Kxc5 49. Nxg4 Rh7 50. Nf6 Rh3+ {+ -+ .}) 47... Rh4 48. Ra8 Ke6 49. Ka5 Rxh2 50. Kb6 Rhh7 51. Ne3 Rhg7 {Rook behind the passed pawn!} 52. Ra4 Kf6 53. Ng4+ Kf5 54. Nh2 (54. Nh6+ Kg6 55. Ng4 Rgf7 {is also losing for White.}) 54... g4 55. Rd4 g3 56. Nf3 g2 0-1

