33. Ke3 f5 $1 {The activation of the black kingside pawn majority is the best way to achieve active play.} 34. g3 $2 ({Good or bad, White had to opt for} 34. f4 $1 e4 35. Bb4 Ra2 36. g4 g6 37. Bc3 Bd7 38. h4 {⩱ .}) 34... g5 $1 {The second line of Black's active defence - White is in trouble.} 35. Bb4 (35. f4 {now is not solving White's problems:} exf4+ 36. gxf4 g4 $1 37. Bb4 Ra1 38. c5 Ra4 39. Be1 Kd5 40. c6 Re4+ {+ -+ .}) 35... Ra2 36. Bd1 $6 ({White is in trouble, but he could still put up a stubborn defence by} 36. Kf2 h5 37. h3 f4 38. gxf4 gxf4 39. Ke1 Rb2 40. Ba5 Rb1+ 41. Kd2 Rh1 42. c5 Kd5 43. c6 Rh2 {∓ .}) 36... Rxh2 37. Kd3 Bb7 38. c5 {It seems that White can still fight...} Bxf3 $1 {But not really!} (38... Bxf3 {If} 39. Bxf3 e4+ 40. Bxe4 fxe4+ 41. Kc3 {(( 41.Kxe4 Rb2 ))} e3 {.}) *

