39. Bb3+ ({After} 39. Bxf3 e4+ 40. Bxe4 fxe4+ 41. Kxe4 Rb2 42. Bc3 Rxb5 43. Bd4 Rb4 {-+ , Black would face no problems to prevail.}) 39... Kd7 $1 (39... Bd5 $2 {looks like the natural response, but White has a nice drawing combination at his disposal:} 40. c6 $1 Bxb3 41. b6 e4+ 42. Kd4 Rc2 43. b7 $1 {(43.c7? Rc4+ 44.Ke3 Kd7 ∓)} Rc4+ 44. Ke3 Rxb4 45. c7 Rxb7 46. c8=Q+ Rd7 {.}) 40. Ba4 ({Winning the black bishop with} 40. c6+ Bxc6 41. bxc6+ Kxc6 {-+ cannot hold for White.}) 40... Ra2 41. c6+ Kc7 42. Bb3 Be4+ 43. Kc3 Ra1 $19 {An improvement over the game.} *

