42. Bb3 Ra8 (42... Be4+ 43. Kc3 Ra1 {-+ was even stronger.}) 43. Be6 Kb6 44. Kc4 Be2+ 45. Kd5 Kxb5 46. Be7 Bc4+ $1 {Simplification!} 47. Kxe5 Bxe6 48. Kxe6 Kxc6 49. Bxg5 {Finally, the smoke has been cleared, and the resulting ending is won for Black.} Ra5 50. Bf4 Rd5 (50... Ra1 51. Kxf5 Kd5 52. g4 Rf1 {-+ is winning as well.}) 51. Be5 Rd8 52. Kxf5 Kd5 53. g4 Rf8+ 54. Bf6 Rg8 55. g5 Rg6 56. Bc3 {Now Black has to re-group: king to [g6] and rook to the queenside, pushing the white king back by checks.} Kd6 57. Bf6 Kd7 58. Be5 Ke7 59. Bf6+ Kf7 60. Be5 Rb6 61. Bf6 Rb5+ 62. Be5 Ra5 63. Ke4 Kg6 64. Bf4 Ra4+ 65. Ke5 $6 ({More stubborn is} 65. Kf3 {, although Black will prevail after} Kf5 66. Bc1 Rd4 67. Be3 Rd3 68. Kf2 Kg4 {-+ .}) 65... Rc4 66. Be3 Rg4 67. Bd2 Rxg5+ $1 68. Kf4 ({After} 68. Bxg5 Kxg5 69. Ke4 Kg4 $1 70. Ke3 Kg3 $1 71. Ke2 Kg2 $1 {, the last black pawn will queen.}) 68... h5 69. Be1 Rg4+ 70. Kf3 Kf5 71. Bg3 h4 72. Bh2 h3 73. Bg3 Rg8 $1 74. Bf4 Rg2 75. Be3 Rg4 $1 0-1

