1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 Ng4 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3 Bg7 10. h3 Ne5 11. f3 Nbc6 12. Bf2 Ng6 13. Qd2 Qa5 14. O-O-O Bd7 15. Kb1 Rc8 16. g3 Nxd4 17. Bxd4 Bxd4 18. Qxd4 Qe5 {To take or to escape? That is the question.} 19. Qf2 $1 {Correctly assessing that the coming exchange sacrifice will not fully suffice, as White's rooks will be easily activated.} Rxc3 $6 {Natural but not the best.} ({Black had to opt for the modest} 19... e6 20. h4 gxh4 21. gxh4 Nf4 22. h5 {⩲ .}) 20. bxc3 Qxc3 {So, Black sacrificed the exchange for a pawn and destroyed White's pawn structure. But White can activate his rooks and have the upper hand.} 21. Rd3 $1 Qa5 22. Qe3 Be6 23. Ra3 Qb4+ 24. Ka1 $1 {The b-file will soon belong to the [h1]-rook!} *

