24... Kd7 $2 {The text makes Black's position even worse.} ({She should have chosen} 24... O-O 25. Be2 Rc8 26. Rb1 Qc5 27. Qxc5 Rxc5 28. Rxb7 Rxc2 29. Rb2 Rc1+ 30. Rb1 Rc2 31. Bxa6 Kg7 {± , where White would have still to prove his advantage.}) 25. Be2 Qc5 26. Rb1 $1 Qxe3 27. Rxe3 Rb8 (27... b5 $6 {would fail to} 28. Ra3 {+- .}) 28. h4 $1 (28. Bxa6 {was natural, but the 'calm' 28.h4 was stronger.}) 28... gxh4 29. f4 $18 (29. f4 f5 30. Bd3 fxe4 31. Bxe4 Bf7 32. Rxb7+ Rxb7 33. Bxb7 hxg3 34. f5 Nh4 35. Rxg3 Nxf5 36. Rc3 Nd4 37. Bxa6 {looks decisive.}) *

