1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. f4 e5 8. Nf5 Qb6 9. Qd2 Qxb2 10. Rb1 Qa3 11. Be2 h6 12. Bh4 exf4 13. O-O g6 14. Rxf4 $1 {White must play actively and the piece sacrifice is a logical follow-up of the previous play.} g5 (14... gxf5 15. Rxf5 {is bad, since White is not only threatening to recapture the knight on [f6], but also to catch the queen with 16.Rb3.}) 15. Rb3 Qa5 16. Nxd6+ Bxd6 17. Qxd6 gxf4 (17... gxh4 18. Rxf6 {is hardly an option for Black.}) 18. Bxf6 (18. Ra3 {, was Teimour Radjabov's move.}) 18... Nxf6 19. Qxf6 Rg8 {[%cal Ga5g5,Gc8e6] The position remains double-edged.} *

