18. Ra3 ({After} 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19. Qxf6 Rg8 {, the position remains double-edged. The important point is that} 20. Nd5 $6 {, is answered by} Qe1+ 21. Bf1 Rxg2+ $1 22. Kxg2 Qxe4+ 23. Kf2 Qxd5 {and Black is somewhat better.}) {How did Hikaru respond in this position?} 18... Qb6+ 19. Qxb6 Nxb6 20. Bxf6 Rg8 {So, White has sacrificed the exchange, gaining the initiative and general active pieces. If Black were able to consolidate and develop naturally, he would take over the situation.} *

