24. c4 b5 $1 25. cxb5 ({Teimour Radjabov thought that} 25. c5 Rb8 26. Nxf4 b4 {would favour Black. At least from the practical point of view, taking on [b5] was certainly a wiser decision: with little time, there was no point in complicating matters.}) 25... axb5 26. Nc3 $2 ({Both players thought that} 26. Bxb5 Rc1+ 27. Kf2 Rxa2+ 28. Kf3 Kd8 {would favour Black, as the black rooks are quite active. But things are far from clear and this line should be followed by White.}) 26... Ba6 $1 27. Kf2 {Here, Hikaru Nakamura missed the chance to set more serious problems for his opponent.} Nc5 {White's task would have been more complicated since there are many possibilities but no clear way to achieve equality.} (27... Nc5 28. Rb4 {(28.Bxc5 Rxc5) (28.Bxb5 Bxb5 29.Rxb5) ( 27...Rd6? will be discussed in our last variation. )}) *

